messages.message:
We have await in loops as blocking for CI which makes sense to me. In this case though, I feel like using await in the while loop is the simplest way to do it since I do want to wait for 1 request and use the result of it to do the next request. Does anyone here prefer another way to do something like this or should I just do a ts-ignore?

```// if grouped by runs, keep calling till last run has all docs fetched
      let allDocReviews: TExpandedReviewObject[] = [];
      let currentParams = { ...params };
      let hasMoreDocs = true;

      while (hasMoreDocs) {
        const currResult = await ReviewDocumentsApi.listReviewDocuments(
          currentParams
        );

        if (currResult.docReviews) {
          allDocReviews = [...allDocReviews, ...currResult.docReviews]; // accumulate the documents
        }

        // update params for next call
        if (
          currResult.docsRemainingForJob &&
          currResult.docsRemainingForJob > 0
        ) {
          currentParams = {
            ...currentParams,
            offset: currentParams.offset
              ? currentParams.offset + PAGING_LIMIT
              : PAGING_LIMIT,
            limit: currResult.docsRemainingForJob,
          };
        } else {
          hasMoreDocs = false;
        }
      }```
